Package testmd

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Permutation
    Defines a test permutation to execute.
    PermutationResult
    Contains the results of a just ran or a previously ran Permutation.
    PermutationResult.Failed
    Result for permutations that failed validation.
    PermutationResult.Invalid
    Results for permutations that are invalid and should be skipped.
    PermutationResult.Unverified
    Result for permutations that are valid but cannot be verified.
    PermutationResult.Valid
    Base class for all Valid results.
    PermutationResult.Verified
    Result for permutations that were successfully verified, either because the Verification logic passed or the results were unchanged since the last verification.
    TestMD
    Entry point class to create a new TestMD test.
    TestMD.ResultsManager
    ResultsManager contains the logic used by TestMD to save results.
    Value
    Container storing an object value plus an ValueFormat to control how the object is Value.serialize()-ed when saved with ResultsWriter
    ValueFormat  
    ValueFormat.ArrayFormat  
    ValueFormat.CollectionFormat
